🧱 Instance Template ---------------------
  👉 A blueprint (configuration) used to create VM instances

  ⚙️ What it contains
    Machine type (e.g., e2-micro)
    OS image (Ubuntu, etc.)
    Disk configuration
    Network (VPC, subnet)
    Metadata / startup script
    Tags & service account

  🔥 Key Characteristics
    Immutable → cannot edit after creation ❌
    To change → create a new template ✅
    Used for consistent VM creation

🚀 Where it is used (Very Important)
  1. Managed Instance Groups (MIG)
    👉 Main use case
    Automatically create & manage VMs
    Auto-scaling
    Auto-healing
  2. Bulk VM creation
    Create multiple identical VMs easily
